I"}<p><a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/perception-is-context-dependent">Perception takes time</a>, it is <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/dynamic-attention-enables-object-permanence">a process, rather than</a> <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/mental-representations-connect-internal-with-external-state">a state</a>. In this view, the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/experiential-scarcity-fosters-appreciation">experience</a> of “now,” the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/experiential-consequences-of-cognitivism">experience</a> of actuality is a phenomenological construct.</p>
